'''''The Essex Reporter''''' is a free [[United States|American]] weekly paper that is centered on [[Essex, Vermont]]. Each Thursday over 8,800 papers are dispersed.<ref>{{cite web|url= http://www.mondotimes.com/1/world/us/45/2584/6098|title= The Essex Reporter|publisher= Mondo Times |accessdate= June 9, 2016}}</ref> The Reporter also covers many other [[Vermont]] towns and cities such as, [[Jericho, Vermont|Jericho]], [[Underhill, Vermont|Underhill]] and [[Winooski, Vermont|Winooski]] - with limited drops in [[Williston, Vermont|Williston]]. ''The Essex Reporter'' is owned and published by Angelo Lynn and Emerson Lynn, who also owns the ''Sun'' in [[Colchester, Vermont]] and who, separately or in combination with other family members, own several other Vermont newspapers.<ref>Christine Haughney, [https://www.nytimes.com/2013/08/16/business/media/vermont-sisters-with-roots-in-news-embrace-small-town-papers.html?pagewanted=all&_r=0 "Vermont Sisters With Roots in News Embrace Small-Town Papers"], ''[[The New York Times]]'', August 15, 2013.</ref><ref>Shay Totten, [http://www.sevendaysvt.com/vermont/all-in-the-media-family/Content?oid=2142318 "All in the Media Family: Vermontâ€™s next-generation publishers chart the future of local news"], ''[[Seven Days (newspaper)|Seven Days]]'', January 12, 2011.</ref>  The paper is a member of [[Champlain Valley]] Newsgroup.<ref>Essex Reporter, [http://www.essexreporter.com/contact/ "Contact"]</ref>

